properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from  Suwannee River to Keaton Beach out 20 NM; Coastal waters from Okaloosa-Walton County Line to Mexico Beach out 20 NM; Coastal Waters From  Ochlockonee River to Apalachicola FL out to 20 Nm; Waters from Suwannee River to Apalachicola FL from 20 to 60 NM; Apalachee Bay or Coastal Waters From Keaton Beach to Ochlockonee River Fl out to 20 Nm; Coastal Waters from Mexico Beach to Apalachicola out 20 NM
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 18 at 4:13AM EST until February 18 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dense fog will reduce visibility to less than one mile at
times.

* WHERE...Nearshore Gulf waters from the Walton-Okaloosa County
line to the Ochlockonee River out 20 nautical miles, Nearshore
Gulf waters from the Ochlockonee River to the Suwannee River
out 20 nautical miles, and Waters from Suwannee River to
Apalachicola FL from 20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM EST /8 AM CST/ Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Low visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EST /8 AM CST/ THIS MORNING
